column5: "31 year old computer geek?", "An all out feeding frenzy that's almost better than sex?"  HAHAHAHA! I'm crying here
It's a ripoff for an underwater light (they want $200) that you can buy at Cabelas for $40
You actually clicked on the link?
It's a very old ad that has been around under several different titles.
How do you know it's the same product unless you clicked the link?  C'mon admit it that banner tantalized you.
Nope, it has been the "evening secret", then the "walleye secret", then the "crappie secret"... and now it's back to the "evening secret"
Yeah yeah  . You wouldn't know that unless you clicked on the link.
Then he was stuck in a PORNADO for 45 minutes!!!!!
I've been clicking for over an hour...still no PORNADO.  False advertising!

I tried four times to write something that wasn't going to get me in trouble...finally I gave up...but you guys are funny Glen is quite right, tho. It is an ad for a light. We don't have porn ads here...though I am sure it would push revenue up quite a bit, however the loss in traffic wouldn't be worth it....lol.
Glenn has finaly seen the light.
